\title{fNIRS: Hemodynamic (8-Channel Hub)}
\taxon{device}
\author{monaduck1069}
\date{2026-04-03}
\tag{fnirs}
\tag{hardware}
\meta{modality}{hemodynamic}
\meta{manufacturer}{PLUX}
\meta{product}{biosignalsplux 8-Channel Kit + fNIRS sensor}
\meta{sku-hub}{820201027}
\meta{sku-sensor}{820201238}
\meta{price-hub}{EUR 3,950}
\meta{price-sensor}{sold separately}

\p{biosignalsplux 8-channel hub with fNIRS sensor. Same single-site fNIRS as the 4-channel Pioneer Kit (bcf-0011) but with 7 free analog channels instead of 3. Hub and fNIRS sensor sold separately (no bundled kit).}

\subtree{\title{fNIRS sensor}
\taxon{remark}
\p{Identical to the 4-channel kit. 1 fNIRS sensor (digital, SPI). Dual-wavelength: 660 nm red + 860 nm infrared. Single photodiode detector. Connects to the ground/reference port. Outputs on virtual channels 9 (red) and 10 (IR). 16-bit resolution, 500 Hz sampling. 1 measurement site.}}

\subtree{\title{Remaining channels}
\taxon{remark}
\p{7 analog channels remain fully available for other biosignals sensors. This is the configuration for multimodal recording: fNIRS + EEG + EMG + ECG simultaneously on a single wireless hub. Same specs as 4-channel: up to 3 kHz per channel, 16-bit, Bluetooth, ~10 hr battery.}}

\subtree{\title{Kit contents}
\taxon{remark}
\p{No bundled fNIRS kit exists for the 8-channel hub. Purchase separately:}
\ul{
\li{1x wireless 8-channel hub (85x54x10 mm, 45 g) -- EUR 3,950}
\li{1x fNIRS sensor (SKU: 820201238) -- priced separately}
\li{1x Bluetooth dongle (included with hub)}
\li{1x medical-grade charger (included with hub)}
\li{Sensors not included -- use PLUX Kit Builder to add}
}}
